  "text": "Using (3.5), (3.11) and (3.16) we see that the logarithmic correction to the free energy is [CITATION_1] Since B \u00b5\u03bd are Grassmann variables the factor is actually L \u2212(D/2\u22122) but the extra minus sign has already been taken into account in (3.5).",
